## MCP Server

The MCP (Model Context Protocol) server is mounted at `/mcp` when enabled.
It exposes tools, resources, and prompts via the streamable-http transport.

**Tools available**:
- `search_documents` — Semantic search across indexed documents
- `ingest_document` — Ingest a document into the knowledge base
- `complete_text` — Generate LLM completions
- `run_rag_query` — Full RAG pipeline (search + generate answer)
- `evaluate_output` — Evaluate quality of LLM-generated answers
{% if use_knowledge_graph %}
- `query_knowledge_graph` — Query entity relationships
- `get_knowledge_graph_stats` — Entity and triplet counts
- `add_knowledge_graph_triplet` — Add a triplet to the graph
{% endif %}
{% if use_external_knowledge_graph %}
- `lookup_external_entity` — Look up entities in Wikidata/DBpedia/ConceptNet
- `get_external_entity_relations` — Get relations for an external entity
{% endif %}

**Resources**: `config://ai-settings`, `status://health`

Connect using any MCP-compatible client:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{ project_slug }}": {
      "url": "http://localhost:8000/mcp"
    }
  }
}
```
{% endif %}
